    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bobbin lace characterized by a fine twisted-and-plaited ground with solid (usually floral) designs outlined with a flat gimp. It was originally produced at Mechelen, now in Belgium.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
